 change on the hydropower potential of Europe: a model-based analysis (2005) Energy Policy, 33, pp. 839-855; Harrison, G.P., Whittington, H.W., Wallace, A.R., Sensitivity of hydropower performance to climate change (2006) International Journal of Power and Energy Systems, 26 (1), pp. 42-48; Thacker, P.D., As the planet heats up, will the topsoil melt away? (2004) Journal of Soil and Water Conservation, 59 (1), pp. 12A-15A; Pritchard, S., Overloaded (2002) International Water Power & Dam Construction, 54 (7), pp. 18-22; (2007) Climate change 2007: impacts, adaptation and vulnerability, , Parry M.L., Canziani O.F., Palutikof J.P., van der Linden P.J., and Hanson C.E. (Eds), CUP, Cambridge, UK; Barnett, T.P., Adam, J.C., Lettenmaier, D.P., Potential impacts of a warming climate on water availability in snow-dominated regions (2005) Nature, 438, pp. 303-309; Macartney, J., Three gorges dam is a disaster in the making, China admits (2007) The Times, , http://www.timesonline.co.uk/tol/news/world/article2537279.ece, Available from:; Brown, L.R., (2008) Plan B 3.0: mobilizing to save civilization, , WW Norton & Co., NY; Moriarty, P., Honnery, D., Global bioenergy: problems and prospects (2007) International Journal of Global Energy Issues, 27 (2), pp. 231-249; Sakr, Y., The fight between fuel and food (2007) Risk Management, 54 (4), pp. 64-68; Field, C.B., Campbell, J.E., Lobell, D.B., Biomass energy: the scale of the potential resource (2008) Trends in Ecology and Evolution, 23 (2), pp. 65-72; Massachusetts Institute of Technology. The future of geothermal energy: impact of enhanced geothermal systems (EGS) on the United States in the 21st century. DOE Contract DE-AC07-051D14517; 2006. Available from: http://geothermal.nrel.govFeiveson, H.A., Faux renaissance: global warming, radioactive waste disposal, and the nuclear future (2007) Arms Control Today, 37 (4), pp. 13-17; Socolow, R.H., Pacala, S.W., A plan to keep carbon in check (2006) Scientific American, pp. 28-35; Pric